# Narrow Trivy ignore for gateway OIDC HTTPS egress.
# The gateway is an OIDC proxy that must reach external identity providers
# (Google, Microsoft, etc.) over HTTPS. Provider IPs are dynamic and cannot
# be pinned to a CIDR list. Egress is restricted to TCP/443 only.
# This ignore targets exactly one rule on one file.
# Format: <rule-id>:<file-path>
#
# AWS-0053: The ALB is intentionally public — it is the entry point for the
# controlled-beta preview. It is protected by Cognito authenticate-cognito
# action with TOTP-required MFA, a WAFv2 web ACL with managed rules, and
# HTTPS-only listener. The internal application container has no direct
# inbound access. This is not an accidental exposure.
AWS-0104:infra/aws-controlled-beta/network.tf
AWS-0053:infra/aws-controlled-beta/compute.tf
